== FreeBSD

The easier way to install Ruby-GNOME2 on FreeBSD is probably through the Ports collection.

Just run the following commands:

  cd /usr/ports/x11/ruby-gnome2-all
  make all install

Do not forget to synchronize your Ports tree before!  

For more information about this, please consult the related section in the ((<FreeBSD Handbook|URL:http://www.freebsd.org/doc/en_US.ISO8859-1/books/handbook/ports.html>)).

